parameters:
\n<Count Noblesse>"Well, I presume you all are already aware of this? No? If
there's anyone who isn't, they can leave right now. Let me
explain once more."
\n<Count Noblesse>"Captain~!!!"
\n<Captain>"Sir!"

\n<Captain>"The other day, we received a notice from that detestable,
vulgar thief \C[14]Phantom Thief "L"\C[0]."

\n<Captain>"I believe our private soldiers have faced him several times
before, but since we also have personnel from the
Adventurers' Guild here today, let me explain about Phantom
Thief "L" once again."

\n<Captain>""L" is so confident and arrogant that he sends a notice
before his thefts. He steals people's wealth and then mocks
them. He is nothing but a lump of exhibitionism and a
despicable villain."

\n<Captain>"Count Noblesse's mansion alone has already suffered 15
incidents, and the entire noble district has experienced
well over 30 thefts."
\n<Adventurer A>"Isn't this place getting robbed too much...?"
\n<Adventurer B>"Aren't the private soldiers incompetent?"
\n<Captain>"Who just spoke out of turn?"

\n<Captain>"It's a shameful truth. We've been outwitted by "L" time and
again, having our money and valuables stolen."

\n<Captain>"But this time it's different! We've fortified the mansion
with a moat, added barriers, traps, and more personnel!
We've strengthened our security even more than before to
ensure everything is foolproof."

\n<Captain>"If by any chance something gets stolen again, you may as
well bury me under a spruce tree. That's how prepared I am
for this challenge."

\n<Captain>"Now, regarding the assignments, our private soldiers will
handle the security inside the mansion, while those
dispatched from the Guild will take care of the outdoor
watch."

\n<Count Noblesse>"And if the notice is to be believed~? The bow moon. In
other words! The crime will take place tonight~."

\n<Count Noblesse>"To the one who captures the cat, furthermore~? Ah,
furthermore! A special reward of a bag of gold will be
given!"
\n<Count Noblesse>"Be encouraged~!! And keep up the spirit~!!"

\n<Rui>"(This seems fun! I'm getting excited♥ I'll catch them and
get lots of money! Fufufu♥)"

\n<Rui>"(A phantom thief, huh... I don't know what kind of person
they are, but stealing from others is wrong. Alright. I'll
catch them!)"
\n<Count Noblesse>...
\n<Count Noblesse>...Captain. I'm counting on you.
\n<Captain>Yes, sir!

\n<Captain>As the previous captain was buried under the spruce tree, I
have been appointed as the new captain. Without further ado,
I will read the advance notice from the phantom thief "L".

\C[14]\n<Captain>Not only the moon shines yellow. Not only wolves howl at the
moon. On a night of a full circle mirror. Just as your face
reflects upon the water's surface. Phantom thief "L"

\n<Captain>Based on this notice, it seems that one of the world's four
great diamonds, \C[14]"The Howling Wolf Stone"\C[0], is
being targeted.

\C[14]\n<Captain>The "Howling Wolf Stone" is so named because it emits a
beautiful yellow light that wolves mistake for the moon and
howl at.

\n<Captain>Normally, even the fact that Count Noblesse possesses it
should be kept a secret of such magnitude.

\n<Captain>This time, we deliberately leaked information about the
Howling Wolf Stone as bait to lure out phantom thief "L".
And he took the bait splendidly.

\n<Adventurer A>The world's four great diamonds... I've seen them in an
encyclopedia before. I can't believe they really exist...
\n<Adventurer B>If it gets stolen, heads will roll...
\n<Captain>Indeed. But that just shows how serious this is.

\n<Captain>A night of a full circle mirror refers to a full moon night,
which is still a few days away. However, given the
importance of the item, we will start guarding it from
tonight.

\n<Captain>Regarding the positions, known private soldiers will be
inside the mansion, while guild reinforcements will handle
the outside. Also, the former captain will be outside as
well.
\n<Former Sergeant>Yes... I'll do my best...

\n<Count Noblesse>This is a kind of gamble. It could even be called a clash of
wills. If the Howling Wolf Stone is stolen, I won't get off
lightly either.

\n<Count Noblesse>But... I will definitely throw Cats into jail and make him
receive his due punishment. Let's make this the last time.
\n<Count Noblesse>...

\n<Rui>(Uncle Count seems different from last time? I have a
strange feeling in my chest...)

\n<Rui>(The Count has a stern look on his face. If only I had
caught him last time... last time...)
\n<Rui>(Ugh... Let's try not to remember too much...)
